The paper focuses on manipulation planning and control for a mobile manipulator to perform shelf replenishment tasks in a supermarket, which falls under the domain of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of a force/tactile sensor, which suggests the involvement of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI) techniques. The integration of reactive grasping control and motion planning also involves control theory (cs.SY) and potentially reinforcement learning (cs.LG) for optimizing the control policies.
